author: Brecca Stoll
description: When nations face a fiscal emergency they turn to the International Monetary Fund (IMF). When they need capital to build roads, energy grids, or water sanitation, they go to the World Bank. Both institutions play essential roles in the international financial system. But Treasury Secretary Scott Bessent believes “mission creep has knocked these institutions off course.” ...
title: Bessent Pushes IMF And World Bank Focus On China, Not Gender And Climate Issues

author: Amanda Prestigiacomo
description: A Colorado woman bled on the emergency room floor while waiting 12 hours for care. A New York man who feared he had appendicitis waited eight hours while repeatedly vomiting and passing out. A cancer survivor in San Francisco waited 28 hours for a doctor to examine her injured leg. title: Why ER Wait Times Are So Out Of Control — And How To Fix Them

author: Gates Garcia
description: If you want to know what the American spirit is, don’t ask a politician. Ask the dad coaching Little League after a 10-hour workday. title: Want To Understand The American Spirit? Don’t Ask A Politician.

author: Luke Rosiak
description: Abigail Spanberger, the former congresswoman running for Virginia’s governorship in next month’s election, is positioning herself as a moderate who opposes “extremism” in an attempt to win the purple state. But that’s not supported by her voting record in Congress.
title: Seeking Virginia’s Votes, Spanberger Talks Like A Moderate. That’s Not How She Voted In Congress.

description: WASHINGTON—A bill to honor a prominent Cuban anti-communist has bipartisan congressional support. Cory Booker isn’t having it. title: Booker Blocks Bipartisan Bill Honoring Anti-Communist Hero

author: Luke Rosiak
description: An aide to a GOP congressman had a flag with a swastika on it behind him during a video conference, triggering outrage on the heels of a story alleging prejudice in the Young Republicans organization. But the aide, Angelo “A.J.” Elia, was a Democrat activist until recently, and served as president of his county’s Young Democrats group in 2022.
